Comment: My opponent moves his king's pawn to free his bishop and queen...
...and I do likewise, with the King's Pawn game...
...and he unleashes his queen to threaten my pawn, with the Patzer opening...
...so I cover it with my queen...
...so he retreats his back to his 3rd rank...
...and I bring up my knight on the queenside, to try to get ahead in development...
...and he attacks it with his light-square bishop...
...so I put it on the attack to threaten the queen and bishop, and possibly to win a pawn and rook...
...forcing her into a passive position...
...so I bring out my dark-square bishop to continue my development, and to take more control of the centre...
...so he brings out his kingside knight...
...but I can't resist capturing it with my knight...
...forcing him to capture it with his queen...
...and I can't resist capturing her with my queen...
...forcing him to distort his pawn structure, doubling on f2 and f3.
I now move up the pawn in front of my light-square bishop to attack his bishop...
...forcing it back...
...and I continue my development with my remaining knight, to regain some control over the centre...
...and he moves his queen's pawn to free his other bishop...
...and I castle kingside to bring a rook into play...
